~ chapter3_star_fragment

Star Fragment: So... you're the one everyone's been talking about.

Player: ...

Player: Then...

Player: Who are you?

Star Fragment: Hahaha...

Star Fragment: It's good to finally meet you, Blessed One.

Star Fragment: I am Pag-asa,
Star Fragment: the Star of Hope.

Player: You seem...

Player: Different.

Star Fragment: Should I be gloomy after finally being free?

Star Fragment: I'd rather celebrate that you found us.

Player: Araw and Hiraya said your memories were returning.

Star Fragment: They are.

Star Fragment: Not all at once...

Star Fragment: Just enough to know we've been asleep for far too long.

Player: The Rebulto...

Star Fragment: Once, people stood before it searching for strength.

Star Fragment: Not because they believed it could solve their problems...

Star Fragment: But because it reminded them they could overcome them.

Player: And they corrupted even that.

Star Fragment: Of course they did.

Star Fragment: Hope frightens those who rule through fear.

Star Fragment: They couldn't destroy it...

Star Fragment: So they convinced people it never existed.

Player: That's why every place I've visited...

Player: ...feels empty.

Star Fragment: Empty...

Star Fragment: But not beyond saving.

Player: You really believe that.

Star Fragment: I have to.

Star Fragment: Hope only dies when no one is willing to carry it.

Star Fragment: Yet here you are.

Player: ...

Player: Then I'll keep carrying it.

Star Fragment: I knew you would.

Star Fragment: Come closer, Blessed One.

Star Fragment: Let my light become one with your own.

=> END